Shell’s Increment Sequence <p>$$ h_t=\lfloor N/2\rfloor,h_k=\lfloor h_{k+1}/2\rfloor $$</p> <pre><code>void Shellsort( ElementType A[ ], int N ) 
{ 
    int i, j, Increment; 
    ElementType Tmp; 
    for ( Increment = N / 2; Increment &gt; 0; Increment /= 2 )  /*h sequence */
        for ( i = Increment; i &lt; N; i++ ) 
        { /* insertion sort */
            Tmp = A[ i ]; 
            for ( j = i; j &gt;= Increment; j -= Increment ) 
                if( Tmp &lt; A[ j-Increment ] )
                    A[ j ] = A[ j-Increment ]; 
                else 
                    break; 
            A[ j ] = Tmp;
        } /* end for-I and for-Increment loops */
}
</code></pre> <ul> <li>[Theorem] The worst-case running time of Shellsort, using Shell’s increments, is  $\Theta( N^2 )$.</li> </ul>

